.TH "luisita" "1" "2026-06-09" "User Commands" "luisita"
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
luisita - Lua-scripted OpenGL graphics environment for real-time demos
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]luisita\f[R] \f[B]-s\f[R] \f[I]script\f[R] [\f[I]options\f[R]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\f[B]luisita\f[R] is a scriptable graphics environment inspired by
Processing, built on top of Lua and C++.
It provides a simple, minimalist API for writing real-time graphical
applications (demos) without requiring deep OpenGL knowledge or manual
C++ memory management.
.PP
A Luisita demo consists of a Lua script that calls the built-in
functions for graphics, image loading, camera control, lighting, fog,
and audio playback.
The script must define at least a \f[B]setup()\f[R] function and a
\f[B]draw(ticks)\f[R] function.
\f[B]setup()\f[R] is called once at startup; \f[B]draw()\f[R] is called
every frame with the elapsed time in milliseconds.
.PP
Luisita uses \f[B]Lua\f[R] for scripting, \f[B]BASS\f[R] for audio
playback, \f[B]OpenGL\f[R] (via GLEW) for rendering, and \f[B]SOIL\f[R]
for image loading.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]-s\f[R] \f[I]filename\f[R], \f[B]\[en]script-name\f[R] \f[I]filename\f[R]
Name of the Lua script to execute.
This option is required.
.TP
\f[B]-w\f[R] \f[I]pixels\f[R], \f[B]\[en]width\f[R] \f[I]pixels\f[R]
Window width in pixels (default: 1024).
.TP
\f[B]-h\f[R] \f[I]pixels\f[R], \f[B]\[en]height\f[R] \f[I]pixels\f[R]
Window height in pixels (default: 768).
.TP
\f[B]\[en]fullscreen\f[R]
Run in fullscreen mode (default: windowed).
.TP
\f[B]\[en]antialias\f[R]
Enable multisample antialiasing (default: disabled).
.TP
\f[B]\[en]antialias-samples\f[R] \f[I]N\f[R]
Number of multisample antialiasing samples to use (default: 4).
Has no effect unless \f[B]\[en]antialias\f[R] is also specified.
.TP
\f[B]-t\f[R] \f[I]seconds\f[R], \f[B]\[en]start-time\f[R] \f[I]seconds\f[R]
Begin playback at \f[I]seconds\f[R] into the timeline (default: 0).
Useful for debugging a specific moment in a demo.
.TP
\f[B]-l\f[R], \f[B]\[en]list-modes\f[R]
List available hardware-accelerated fullscreen resolutions and exit.
.TP
\f[B]-?\f[R], \f[B]\[en]help\f[R]
Show a brief usage summary and exit.
.SH LUA API
.PP
The following global functions are available inside Lua scripts:
.SS Setup and control
.TP
\f[B]setupIsDone\f[R]()
Signal that the \f[B]setup()\f[R] function has completed initialisation.
.TP
\f[B]quit\f[R]()
Request application exit.
.TP
\f[B]windowTitle\f[R](\f[I]title\f[R])
Set the window title string.
.TP
\f[B]width\f[R](), \f[B]height\f[R]()
Return the current window width or height in pixels.
.TP
\f[B]trace\f[R](\f[I]message\f[R])
Print \f[I]message\f[R] to standard output (debugging aid).
.SS 2D / 3D primitives
.TP
\f[B]beginShape\f[R]([\f[I]type\f[R]]), \f[B]endShape\f[R]()
Begin and end a vertex sequence.
\f[I]type\f[R] can be SHAPE_POINTS, SHAPE_LINES, SHAPE_LINE_STRIP,
SHAPE_TRIANGLES, SHAPE_TRIANGLE_STRIP, SHAPE_QUADS, SHAPE_QUAD_STRIP, or
SHAPE_POLYGON.
.TP
\f[B]vertex\f[R](\f[I]x\f[R], \f[I]y\f[R][, \f[I]z\f[R]]), \f[B]normal\f[R](\f[I]nx\f[R], \f[I]ny\f[R], \f[I]nz\f[R])
Add a vertex or surface normal to the current shape.
.TP
\f[B]line\f[R](\f[I]x1\f[R], \f[I]y1\f[R], \f[I]x2\f[R], \f[I]y2\f[R]), \f[B]triangle\f[R](\f[I]x1\f[R], \f[I]y1\f[R], \f[I]x2\f[R], \f[I]y2\f[R], \f[I]x3\f[R], \f[I]y3\f[R])
Draw a line or triangle directly.
.TP
\f[B]stipple\f[R](), \f[B]noStipple\f[R]()
Enable or disable line stippling.
.SS Colour
.TP
\f[B]background\f[R](\f[I]r\f[R], \f[I]g\f[R], \f[I]b\f[R][, \f[I]a\f[R]])
Set the background (clear) colour.
.TP
\f[B]fill\f[R](\f[I]r\f[R], \f[I]g\f[R], \f[I]b\f[R][, \f[I]a\f[R]]), \f[B]noFill\f[R]()
Set or disable the fill colour for shapes.
.TP
\f[B]stroke\f[R](\f[I]r\f[R], \f[I]g\f[R], \f[I]b\f[R][, \f[I]a\f[R]]), \f[B]noStroke\f[R]()
Set or disable the outline colour for shapes.
.TP
\f[B]color\f[R](\f[I]r\f[R], \f[I]g\f[R], \f[I]b\f[R][, \f[I]a\f[R]]), \f[B]colorMode\f[R](\f[I]mode\f[R])
Set the current drawing colour or the colour interpretation mode.
.TP
\f[B]strokeWeight\f[R](\f[I]w\f[R]), \f[B]pointSize\f[R](\f[I]s\f[R])
Set the stroke width or point size in pixels.
.SS Images and textures
.TP
\f[B]loadImage\f[R](\f[I]filename\f[R])
Load an image file and return a texture identifier.
.TP
\f[B]image\f[R](\f[I]texId\f[R], \f[I]x\f[R], \f[I]y\f[R], \f[I]w\f[R], \f[I]h\f[R])
Draw texture \f[I]texId\f[R] at (\f[I]x\f[R], \f[I]y\f[R]) with size
\f[I]w\f[R] × \f[I]h\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]useTexture\f[R](\f[I]texId\f[R]), \f[B]noTexture\f[R]()
Bind or unbind a texture for subsequent geometry.
.SS Camera and projection
.TP
\f[B]ortho\f[R]([\f[I]w\f[R], \f[I]h\f[R]]), \f[B]restoreProjection\f[R]()
Switch to orthographic (2D) projection or restore the previous one.
.TP
\f[B]camera\f[R](\f[I]eyeX\f[R], \f[I]eyeY\f[R], \f[I]eyeZ\f[R], \f[I]centerX\f[R], \f[I]centerY\f[R], \f[I]centerZ\f[R], \f[I]upX\f[R], \f[I]upY\f[R], \f[I]upZ\f[R])
Position the 3D camera (equivalent to gluLookAt).
.TP
\f[B]perspective\f[R](\f[I]fov\f[R], \f[I]aspect\f[R], \f[I]zNear\f[R], \f[I]zFar\f[R])
Set a perspective projection.
.TP
\f[B]depthTest\f[R](), \f[B]noDepthTest\f[R]()
Enable or disable OpenGL depth testing.
.SS Blending
.TP
\f[B]blending\f[R](\f[I]mode\f[R]), \f[B]noBlending\f[R]()
Enable a blending mode or disable blending entirely.
\f[I]mode\f[R] is one of BLENDING_ALPHABLEND, BLENDING_ADDITIVE,
BLENDING_SUBSTRACTIVE, BLENDING_MULTIPLY, BLENDING_COLORMULTIPLY.
.SS Lights
.TP
\f[B]lightEnabled\f[R](\f[I]n\f[R]), \f[B]noLights\f[R]()
Enable OpenGL light \f[I]n\f[R] or disable all lights.
.TP
\f[B]lightPosition\f[R](\f[I]n\f[R], \f[I]x\f[R], \f[I]y\f[R], \f[I]z\f[R]), \f[B]lightAmbient\f[R](\f[I]n\f[R], \f[I]r\f[R], \f[I]g\f[R], \f[I]b\f[R], \f[I]a\f[R])
Set the position or ambient colour of light \f[I]n\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]lightDiffuse\f[R](\f[I]n\f[R], \f[I]r\f[R], \f[I]g\f[R], \f[I]b\f[R], \f[I]a\f[R]), \f[B]lightSpotDirection\f[R](\f[I]n\f[R], \f[I]x\f[R], \f[I]y\f[R], \f[I]z\f[R])
Set the diffuse colour or spot direction of light \f[I]n\f[R].
.SS Fog
.TP
\f[B]fogMode\f[R](\f[I]mode\f[R]), \f[B]fogDensity\f[R](\f[I]d\f[R]), \f[B]fogStartEnd\f[R](\f[I]start\f[R], \f[I]end\f[R]), \f[B]fogColor\f[R](\f[I]r\f[R], \f[I]g\f[R], \f[I]b\f[R], \f[I]a\f[R])
Configure OpenGL fog.
\f[I]mode\f[R] is one of FOG_NONE, FOG_LINEAR, FOG_EXP, FOG_EXP2.
.SS Audio
.TP
\f[B]loadMusicStream\f[R](\f[I]filename\f[R])
Load an audio file and return a stream handle.
.TP
\f[B]playMusicStream\f[R](\f[I]handle\f[R])
Start playback of stream \f[I]handle\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]isMusicStreamFinished\f[R](\f[I]handle\f[R])
Return true when stream \f[I]handle\f[R] has finished playing.
.TP
\f[B]getMusicStreamTime\f[R](\f[I]handle\f[R]), \f[B]getMusicStartPosition\f[R]()
Return the current playback position in seconds, or the value passed via
\f[B]\[en]start-time\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Run the bundled hello-world script in a 1280 × 720 window:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
luisita -s samples/001-hello.lua -w 1280 -h 720
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Run a demo in fullscreen with antialiasing from the 30-second mark:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
luisita -s demo.lua --fullscreen --antialias -t 30
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
List available fullscreen resolutions:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
luisita --list-modes
\f[R]
.fi
